<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB01910</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT TO ADDRESSING THE ISSUE OF LABOR CONTRACTUALIZATION BY PROVIDING STANDARDS FOR TERM OR FIXED-PERIOD EMPLOYMENT, AMENDING FOR THE PURPOSE PRESIDENTIAL DECREE NO. 442, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS ꞌTHE LABOR CODE OF THE PHILIPPINESꞌ </td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to amend the present Labor Code so as to substantially implement it by providing standards specific to term or fixed-period employment, including but not limited to: a clear definition of term or fixed-period employment; requisites for validity of term or fixed-period employment; and condition for regularization of term or fixed-period employment.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>VILLARICA, LINABELLE RUTH R.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-07-26</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Welfare</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>MOTHER BILL:&nbspHB06908</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON LABOR AND EMPLOYMENT ON 2016-08-03</td></tr></table>